  "original_title": "\u0db8\u0db8 \u0d87\u0db8\u0dad\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0db8\u0dca \u0db7\u0dcf\u0dbb \u0d9c\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dda \u0db1\u0dd1 - \u0dc4\u0dbb\u0dca\u0dc2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "I will not accept ministership - Harsha",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Member of Parliament, Mr. Acharya Harsha de Silva says that the information reported in some media that he is ready to accept a ministerial position is false.",
        "He said that he did not negotiate with any party in the government for a ministerial post or any other position and that former President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa declared that an all-party government is needed to get out of the economic crisis that Sri Lanka was facing.",
        "In his Twitter account, he states that in order to get rid of the economic crisis that Sri Lanka is currently facing, severe reforms have been implemented.",
        "For that, party leaders should put aside their political ideologies for about 9-12 months and work for a common agenda, he added."
      ],
